question.value:
We recruit participants through the SONA-System of University of Mannheim and flyers. The psychology students will be rewarded with 0,50 “VPN-Stunden” (credits earned for participating in psychology studies). 

Inclusion criteria:
-	German as native language (or before the age of 6 acquired);
-	age: 18-35 years;
-	no history of depression, anxiety disorders, PTSD, or other acute psychiatric disorders in the last 6 months.

Data collection is based on the open-source experiment builder lab.js (Henninger et al., 2022) and hosted on the OpenLab website (Shevchenko, 2022). After completing the informed consent and the demographic questionnaire, the participants study word pairs for six minutes, followed by two minutes of solving math equations. The recognition test and cued-recall test could last each approximately five minutes. At the end of the study, the participants receive information about our research question (debriefing). The experiment is expected to last approximately 30 minutes.

